text: First time eating this stall, food was simply divine! After eating the pork chops with pasta and the chicken chop with pasta also (my fwen ordered) I feel like a new man.. I feel reborn and most important my love for western food has been revived like a phoenix...

Waited 20mins for the $18 tomahawk and it was reasonably good. The spices was abundant and the char taste turns out pretty well.

It was worth the $18 comparing to what you would get elsewhere. it is suitated in a coffeeshop so manage your expectations.
Ordered the sirloin steak (medium rare) for $13.90. It came slightly overcooked, but still tasted pretty good. Sides were tasty, and overall, great value for the price.

Always like this Axe Western food, we always take away    ...Portion Big for us...Must order 3side dish one...I told them 2x side dish they blur alr dont know how to sell..haha. Must try no regret. Value for money. ðŸ˜‹ðŸ˜‹

2024.11.22

Was collecting car fm car workshop . Decided to get a quick bite. Did a Google search and this came up.
For $8, the two slices of grilled pork chop, pasta, salad, and potato mash is pretty substantial. Grilled pork chop is a 7/10. Pasta is overcooked. Mash tasted like premix. lettuce is normal. i would have rated a 3 but for the price point, it deserves a 4.
